node.title: Parliament House closed and Greens leader in isolation after staffer tests positive to COVID-19
node.alt: Adam Bandt speaks at Parliament House.
node.description: Federal Greens leader Adam Bandt is isolating after one of his staff members tests positive for COVID-19.
node.content: ["Parliament House has been closed and Federal Greens leader Adam Bandt is isolating after one of his staff members tested positive for COVID-19.\u00a0", "A spokesperson for Mr Bandt said the staff member, who was in Canberra during the last sitting week of parliament\u00a0returned the positive result in Melbourne.\u00a0", "The staff member is fully vaccinated, according to the spokesperson.\u00a0", "\"Mr Bandt has been tested and is isolating until he receives a result. He is fully vaccinated and not symptomatic,\" they said.", "\"Other members of the team have been tested and returned negative results.\"", "Health authorities in the ACT are now trying to determine if the staff member was infectious while he was in the capital.\u00a0", "Federal parliament has been closed to the public as a precautionary measure, according to the Department of Parliamentary Services.\u00a0", "\"ACT Health are working to identify possibly close contacts, and exposure locations at Parliament House and elsewhere in the ACT between November 30 and December 2, 2021. More information will be provided as soon as it is available,\" the statement said.", "The ACT recorded seven new COVID-19 infections on Saturday and announced its\u00a0first case of the Omicron variant on Friday.\u00a0"]
